        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1956-01-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1956-01-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="43"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d43">
                <head>43. Diary Entry by the President<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d43fn1"
                        >Source: <persName corresp="#p_EDD1">Eisenhower</persName> Library, Whitman
                        File, DDE Diaries. Secret.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1956-01-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 19, 1956</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Ambassador Conant came to see me to bring me personal messages from Chancellor
                        <persName corresp="#p_AK1">Adenauer</persName>
                    <note n="2" xml:id="d43fn2">No oral or written messages from <persName
                            corresp="#p_AK1">Adenauer</persName> have been found in Department of
                        State files or the <persName corresp="#p_EDD1">Eisenhower</persName>
                        Library.</note> and the report that the Chancellor’s health, at 81, seems to
                    be improving daily. He also expressed to me his (Conant’s) great concern in
                    establishing in Europe a six-power community for handling of activities in
                    nuclear science in that region. He points out that in some of these countries
                    activities could well go underground if we did not move in the direction of the
                    community development. I agreed with him.</p>
            </div>
